        }

            position: absolute;

<body>
    <div id="game-container">
        <canvas id="game-canvas"></canvas>
        <div id="health-bar">
            <div id="health-fill"></div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <script>
        const canvas = document.getElementById('game-canvas');
        const ctx = canvas.getContext('2d');

        const levels = [
            { image: 'data:image/jpeg;base64,', color: 'rgba(255, 0, 0, 0.5)' },
            { image: 'data:image/jpeg;base64,', color: 'rgba(0, 255, 0, 0.5)' },
            { image: 'https://uploads8.wikiart.org/images/vincent-van-gogh.jpg!Portrait.jpg', color: 'rgba(0, 0, 255, 0.5)' }
            // Replace with paths to your picture images and colors
        ];

        const healthBar = document.getElementById('health-fill');
        let currentLevel = 0;
        let health = 100;
        let paintColor = 'rgba(255, 0, 0, 0.5)'; // Default color
        const splotches = [];

        function loadLevel(level) {
            const img = new Image();
            img.src = levels[level].image;
            img.onload = function() {
                canvas.width = img.width;
                canvas.height = img.height;
                ctx.drawImage(img, 0, 0);
                updateHealth(100); // Reset health for each level
            };
        }

        function updateHealth(amount) {
            health = Math.max(0, Math.min(100, health + amount));
            healthBar.style.width = health + '%';

            if (health <= 0) {
                setTimeout(nextLevel, 500); // Wait before moving to the next level
            }
        }


        function nextLevel() {
            if (currentLevel < levels.length - 1) {
                currentLevel++;
                loadLevel(currentLevel);
            } else {
                alert('Congratulations! You have completed all levels.');
            }
        }

        canvas.addEventListener('click', function(event) {
            const rect = canvas.getBoundingClientRect();
            const x = event.clientX - rect.left;
            const y = event.clientY - rect.top;

            // Decrease health on click
            updateHealth(-10); // Decrease health for each click
        });

        // Initialize the first level
        loadLevel(currentLevel);
    </script>
</body>
